<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><ul><li>Transform seat=
ing assignments into a fun puzzle by using index cards or sticky notes on a=
 poster board.</li><li>Finalize your guest list first, then group guests by=
 common interests like kids' ages or travel stories.</li><li>Consider your =
venue's layout to decide where guests like parents and little ones should b=
e seated for comfort.</li></ul></div>
</div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_2-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-htm=
l mntl-sc-block-html"> Making your wedding seating chart can often be one o=
f the most stressful parts of <a href=3D"https://www.brides.com/story/bride=
s-wedding-checklist-custom-wedding-to-do-list" data-component=3D"link" data=
-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">the pl=
anning process</a>. Whether you're hosting 50 or 300 loved ones at your nup=
tials, thinking about which attendees should sit next to each other=E2=80=
=94and which should be placed on opposite sides of the room=E2=80=94may fee=
l overwhelming. In addition to figuring out how to group your friends and f=
amily, you'll also need to consider the layout of your venue by looking at =
<a href=3D"https://www.brides.com/story/how-to-plan-your-wedding-reception-=
layout" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"int=
ernalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">the space's floor plan.</a> Without this esse=
ntial sheet, you won't know how many tables you'll need=E2=80=94or what sha=
pe of table may (or may not!) work. <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-adslot mnt=
l-sc-block-adslot-inline"></span>As a result, it's crucial to request this =
information before you start crafting your seating chart. "Ask for several =
layouts based on the guest count to see what the options are, including the=
 plotting of dance floors, photo booths, etc.," says Chanda Daniels, the fo=
under and creative director of&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.instagram.com/cd=
_chandadaniels/" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-ty=
pe=3D"externalLink" data-ordinal=3D"3" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">C=
handa Daniels Planning + Design</a>. "That will help you determine where to=
 seat the guests."
</p>
