v>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_20-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-s=
ubheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadin=
g__text"> Create an Electronic or Physical Seating Chart </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_21-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> There are two ways you can organize your seating ch=
art: electronically or by hand. If you go the virtual route, many sites off=
er a drag-and-drop seating tool, allowing you to switch up your arrangement=
s easily. However, even if you opt to create your chart by hand, you can st=
ill make the editing process seamless. Sketch your tables on a piece of pos=
ter board, and write every guest's name on an individual sticky note. When =
you suddenly change your mind about a guest's assigned table, you'll be abl=
e to move them around without a problem. Another option? A large whiteboard=
 and dry-erase markers.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_22-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_23-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
featuredlink mntl-sc-block-featuredlink mntl-block related-link"><a href=3D=
"https://www.brides.com/story/digital-seating-charts-wedding-planning" rel=
=3D"nocaes" id=3D"mntl-sc-block-featuredlink__link_2-0" class=3D"mntl-sc-bl=
ock-featuredlink__link mntl-text-link " data-tracking-container=3D"true" da=
ta-tracking-id=3D"featured-link"><span class=3D"link__wrapper">5 Free Digit=
al Wedding Seating Chart Templates to Simplify the Planning Process</span><=
/a></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_24-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_25-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-s=
ubheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadin=
g__text"> Keep Your Venue in Mind </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_26-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> The layout of your venue will play an important rol=
e in your seating chart. For example, your closest friends will likely want=
 to be in the center of the celebration, while older relatives may prefer t=
o be a bit further away from your band or DJ. And if you have any <a class=
=3D"recommendation-inline-link" href=3D"https://www.brides.com/how-to-make-=
wedding-accessible-6281075" link-destination-recommendation=3D"true" data-c=
omponent=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" dat=
a-ordinal=3D"1">guests in wheelchairs</a>, make sure they have adequate spa=
ce to safely move around.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_27-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_28-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
callout--tips beauty-sc-block-callout mntl-sc-block-callout mntl-block them=
e-tips" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-container=
=3D"true"><div id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout-body_1-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-=
block-callout-body mntl-text-block"><p>Seat younger guests who will be danc=
ing all night near the band or the DJ, so they have easy access to the danc=
e floor.</p></div></div>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_29-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-s=
ubheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadin=
g__text"> Figure Out Where Your Parents Will Sit </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_30-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> Traditionally, <a href=3D"https://www.brides.com/st=
ory/parents-wedding-reception-seating" data-component=3D"link" data-source=
=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">all of the pa=
rents</a> share a table at the reception, along with grandparents and any s=
iblings that aren't in the wedding party. However, this arrangement can bec=
ome a bit more complicated if <a href=3D"https://www.brides.com/story/prepa=
re-divorced-parents-before-the-wedding" data-component=3D"link" data-source=
=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">your or your =
partner's partners are divorced</a>. If things are tense between certain ke=
y individuals, consider having two tables that are equally close to the hea=
d table, and put one at each table to ensure no one feels uncomfortable or =
left out. Another option: Consider seating them at the same rectangular tab=
le=E2=80=94but at opposite ends (and try to make the table <em>long</em>).
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_31-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_32-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-s=
ubheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadin=
g__text"> Keep Your Wedding Party Close </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_33-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> When making your seating chart, you'll need to deci=
de whether you'd prefer to have <a class=3D"recommendation-inline-link" hre=
f=3D"https://www.brides.com/story/head-table-wedding-reception-seating" lin=
k-destination-recommendation=3D"true" data-component=3D"link" data-source=
=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">a head table<=
/a>, a sweetheart table, or something else entirely. If you do opt for <a c=
lass=3D"recommendation-inline-link" href=3D"https://www.brides.com/story/sw=
eetheart-table-ideas" link-destination-recommendation=3D"true" data-compone=
nt=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordi=
nal=3D"2">a sweetheart table</a>, consider tapping the members of your wedd=
ing party to be the "hosts" of other tables. Seat them with their dates and=
 a group of other mutual friends in close proximity to the dance floor.<br>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_34-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_35-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-s=
ubheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadin=
g__text"> Enlist Your Parents' Help to Seat Their Friends </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_36-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> If you have no idea where to seat your parents' clo=
se friends, ask your mother or father to help arrange those tables. For exa=
mple, if there's room at the family table(s), your parents will likely have=
 an opinion on which attendees they would like seated next to them.<br>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_37-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_38-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-s=
ubheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadin=
g__text"> Skip the Singles Table </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_39-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> Even if you've been dying to fix your former cowork=
er up with your cousin, resist the urge to create a separate "singles" tabl=
e, as such an arrangement might embarrass your guests. In a similar vein, a=
voiding seating your unmarried friend at a table full of married couples. U=
se your best judgment, and try to be sensitive to how attendees may feel.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_40-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
<h3 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_41-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-s=
ubheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-block-subheadin=
g__text"> Consider a Kids' Table </span> </h3>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_42-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> If you have several children as guests at your wedd=
ing, consider seating them together at a separate kids' table, where you ca=
n arrange for <a href=3D"https://www.brides.com/kids-activities-weddings-62=
65482" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"inte=
rnalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">engaging activities</a> and/or crafts to keep =
them occupied. And while it might be tempting to put them in a corner, defi=
nitely do not put the kids' table <em>too</em> far away from where their pa=
rents are sitting. Younger children might get anxious when they look around=
 and don't see their parents anywhere (and vice versa). On the other hand, =
if <a class=3D"recommendation-inline-link" href=3D"https://www.brides.com/s=
tory/where-the-flower-girl-tradition-comes-from" link-destination-recommend=
ation=3D"true" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=
=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">your flower girl</a> and <a class=3D"r=
ecommendation-inline-link" href=3D"https://www.brides.com/story/flower-girl=
-ring-bearer-etiquette-who-pays-where-they-sit" link-destination-recommenda=
tion=3D"true" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=
=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"3">ring bearer</a> are the only children =
present, seat them with their parents.<br>
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_43-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block beauty-sc-block-=
adslot mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block u-no-article-width-restriction"></di=
v>
